          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Temporary price data. Calculated as 90% of purchasers price based on: Price for industrial users from IEA Key world energy statistics 2004 (www.iea.org). In addition, regarding label-certified electricity, the Swiss government has a market instrument for renewable energy which is calculated as the difference between the market price and the production price. This was started in 2009 and is 0.45 Rp/kWh (http://www.bfe.admin.ch/themen/00612/02073/index.html?lang=de). Therefore, the production price of label certified energy is assumed to be the supplyer price plus the 0.45Rp/kWh.The unit conversion from CH to EUR is based on the ecoinvent unit conversion file (1 CHF2005 = 0.644 EUR2005).</comment>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The production volume is valid for the year 2021. See general comment for sources.</productionVolumeComment>
